{{Infobox journal | title = Environmental Philosophy | cover = envirophilcover2.gif | editor = Ted Toadvine | discipline = [[Philosophy]], [[ethics]] | formernames = | abbreviation = Environ. Philos. | publisher = [[Philosophy Documentation Center]] | country = | frequency = Biannual | history = 2004–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = https://www.pdcnet.org/envirophil | link2 = https://www.pdcnet.org/envirophil/toc | link2-name = Journal content with abstracts | JSTOR = | OCLC = 68552984 | LCCN = cn2006300749 | CODEN = | ISSN = 1718-0198 | eISSN = 2153-8905 }} '''Environmental Philosophy''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that publishes articles, reviews, and discussions relevant to all areas of environmental philosophy. The journal was established in 2004 and is edited by Ted Toadvine at Penn State University. It is sponsored by the [[International Association for Environmental Philosophy]] and published by the [[Philosophy Documentation Center]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pdcnet.org/envirophil |title=Journal home page |accessdate=26 November 2018 |publisher=Philosophy Documentation Center}}</ref> The journal is published twice yearly in May and November issues.
