==Types of Competition==
===Surana & Surana International Technology Law Moot Court Competition=== Established in 2002.<ref>{{cite web|title=Surana & Surana International Technology Law Moot Court Competition, 2013|url=http://www.lawctopus.com/12th-surana-surana-international-technology-law-moot-court-competition/|publisher=Law Octopus|accessdate=1 Feb 2013}}</ref> with the aim of training the participants in application of laws to challenges posed by the rapid technological advancements, this moot focuses on the developments in Public and Private International Law and has ingredients of international trade and operations of multi national corporations. Themes covered till date include Information Technology, Biotechnology, Intellectual Property, Space laws, Aviation, Nuclear proliferation, Communication, Cyber Crime and Broadcasting. Participants gain considerable expertise in the respective domains on which the issues are framed.
